explanation: The solution utilizes a iterative approach to convert the integer to base -2. It repeatedly calculates the remainder when dividing by -2, appending "1" if the remainder is non-negative and "0" otherwise. The process continues until the quotient becomes zero. The resulting string is then reversed to obtain the correct base -2 representation. This approach leverages the inherent logarithmic nature of repeated division, resulting in efficient time complexity. The space complexity is also logarithmic due to the potential size of the resulting binary string.

